cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of real-time, accurate, and robust pupil detection using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of eye-tracking in real-world scenarios, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the use of probability distribution for refinement can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
